data.title: Growing up in Pelham Parkway in the Bronx, I never dreamed when I grew up I’d be in the Bronx Jewish Hall of Fame, have a street named...
data.meta_description:
5,856 likes, 125 comments - official_renee_taylor on September 30, 2021: "Growing up in Pelham Parkway in the Bronx, I never dreamed when I grew up I’d be in the Bronx Jewish Hall of Fame, have a street named after me (on the Grand Concourse in the Bronx), be an @theacademy Nominee, or a @televisionacad winner! ⁠
⁠
At 5 years old, I won the Charming Child Contest by Daily News and couldn't get enough of the stage. This led me down a path to marry the very handsome writer and actor, Joe Bologna. Nothing was more fulfilling than having our son, Gabriel, direct us both in Joe's last funny movie, Tango Shalom, what I like to call a 'Kosher version of #SaturdayNightFever'!⁠
⁠
#TangoShalom is now out in theaters! Be sure to get your tuchuses in a seat and let me know what you think of @tangoshalom!⁠".
